Detailed Description

Class Definition CENABLE_ACCESSSPEC for LLRP message ENABLE_ACCESSSPEC.

  • Document Reference LLRP Specification Section 11.1.5

  • Document Reference LLRP Specification Section 16.1.21

This message is issued by the Client to the Reader. Upon receiving the message, the Reader moves the AccessSpec corresponding to the AccessSpecID in this message from the Disabled state to the Active state. The Reader executes this access-spec until it gets a DISABLE_ACCESSSPEC or a DELETE_ACCESSSPEC from the Client. The AccessSpec takes effect with the next (and subsequent) inventory rounds.

AccessSpecID: If set to 0, all AccessSpecs are enabled.

void LLRP::CENABLE_ACCESSSPEC::assimilateSubParameters (  CErrorDetails *  pError  )  [virtual]
 

Assimilates the decoded sub-parameters into m_listAllSubParameters.

After fields are decoded, the CDecoder itself takes care of gathering the subparameters into m_listAllSubParameters. Once the end of the enclosing TLV (or message) is reached this assimilateSubParameters() function is called to create parameter refrences from the primary member variables.
